EXP NO 3 

Stepper motor interface with waveform generation using 8051 trainer kit

OBJECTIVE

To write programs to interface stepper motor to microcontroller.

LEARNING OUTCOMES
•	Understand the working principle of stepper motors and the concept of step angles.
•	Program the microcontroller to toggle between clockwise and anti-clockwise rotation.

ALGORITHM

Step1: Start.
Step2: Enter the first values of rotation sequence to desired memory location.
Step3: Set the count value as 4.
Step4: Copy the value of rotation sequence to A.
 Step5: Call delay
 Step6: Copy control word FFC0 TO DPTR
Step7: Copy the value of rotation sequence to FFC0.
Step8: Decrement the count go to step if count is non zero.
Step 9: Stop

